fazzzoola:  Howard, serious question about BBO:  Do you know if the hands BBO deals out are truly random?|
PG| ***** 51 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Many people feel that computer dealt hands, on BBO or in live bridge clubs, are "fixed" and they throw out hands. But that is not true. They are truly random. People feel they are more distributional. When you manually deal cards out by shuffling, most people don't shuffle the cards enough. |
PG| ***** 52 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|You need to shuffle the cards with good shuffling technique at least 6 or 7 times. So manually dealt hands tend to be much flatter than random hands because they are not truly random. They are actually flatter than random. That's why people think computer dealt hands are deliberately set up for wilder distributions because they are used to the less random manual deals. |
PG| ***** 53 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|But in fact computer dealt hands are really random and manually dealt hands are not. Poor shuffling makes them flatter because each trick often contains 4 cards of the same suit in a row. Therefore if you dealt a hand without shuffling, everyone would get 1 card in that suit when there are 4 of the same suit in a row.|
