^B@2^*BAndy Hung: ^*N|cp||at|Play: It might seem a bit odd as to why North (your RHO) played the @SQ rather than the @SA on the first trick. Your RHO wanted to keep an entry back to their partner's hand with the spades. By winning with the @SA and a spade return, you, declarer, will be able to hold up the spade suit as many times as you want. Why is this relevant, you might ask. Well imagine if your spade suit was K x x x (with no intermediate cards).|
